<http://example.org/fair-assessment#> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology> .
<http://example.org/fair-assessment#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/created> "2025-02-01"^^<http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date> .
<http://example.org/fair-assessment#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/creator> "Gabriele Tuozzo" .
<http://example.org/fair-assessment#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/description> "An ontology for modeling FAIR principle assessment results for digital objects, with support for temporal tracking and detailed sub-principle evaluation."@en .
<http://example.org/fair-assessment#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/title> "FAIR Assessment Ontology"@en .
<http://example.org/fair-assessment#> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "This ontology provides comprehensive FAIR assessment modeling. It reuses the official FAIR Vocabulary (https://w3id.org/fair/principles/terms/) for principle and sub-principle definitions."@en .
<http://example.org/fair-assessment#> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#versionInfo> "1.0" .
